10 SUMMARY
1111 This amendment amends the bill by changing the date by which the Department of
1122 Administrative and Financial Services, Bureau of General Services is required to ensure
1133 that if the only public restroom within a public building that is equipped with a diaper
1144 changing station is restricted to persons of a specific gender, another public restroom within
1155 the building that is available to persons of other genders is equipped with a diaper changing
1166 station that is physically safe, sanitary and appropriate to January 1, 2029 or an earlier date
1177 if funding allows, whichever occurs first. The amendment also modifies an exception by
1188 removing the requirement specifying that another restroom with a diaper changing station
1199 that is accessible to an individual must be on the same floor. The amendment also adds a
2200 provision that permits the Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Bureau of
2211 General Services to accept outside funds for the purchase, construction and installation of
2222 diaper changing stations. The amendment adds an appropriations and allocations section.
